==English==

A form of [[bright]] ''(adjective)''

===Bright: Light===
====Adjective====
'''bright'''
*full of light, [[shining]]
**''The lights are too bright in here - they're hurting my eyes''
====Verb====
'''to brighten'''
*to (cause to) become lighter:
**''The room was small and dark, without so much as a ray of light to brighten the gloom''
====Adverb====
'''brightly'''
*''a brightly lit room''
====Noun====
''''brightness''''
*''The brightness of the snow made him blink''

===Bright: Colour===
====Adjective====
'''bright'''
*strong in colour
**''He said hello and I felt my face turn bright red''
====Adverb====
'''brightly'''
*''brightly coloured flowers''

===Bright: Intelligent===
====Adjective====
'''bright'''
*(of a person) clever and quick to learn
**''They were bright children, always asking questions''

===Bright: Happy===
====Adjective====
'''bright'''
*full of hope for success or happiness
**''You're very bright and cheerful this morning''
====Verb====
'''to brighten'''
*to (cause to) become happy or hopeful
**''Her eyes brightened when she saw him enter the room''
====Adverb====
'''brightly'''
*''Despite her fear, she spoke brightly to the group''

